    It's hard for me to write these words- in fact, I don't even know where to start. <br>
    I woke up today with a heart that ached so badly it threatened to burst out of <br>
    my chest. It's a different kind of pain, the crippling kind that made me want to curl <br>
    up into a ball and cry cry cry it out. It feels like without you, I suddenly became lost<br>
    in this empty world. You are my other half. Without you, I don't feel complete. <br><br>
    To be honest, I think it's still hitting me. Slowly, certainly, it is hitting me with the <br>
    magnitude that you're no longer mine. I've cried so much and hurt so much- I don't know <br>
    if I can accept that you're gone.<br><br>
    I love you so much, Jenna. I gave you my everything, I tried so hard to make you happy. <br>
    And now, I understand that it was too much. I'm so angry- angry at myself for not seeing it<br>
    angry at the situation for punishing me so. I reflect back on my behavior as a boyfriend and <br>
    I just... I can say that I really really really did try. I did everything to make you happy, <br>
    and in the end, perhaps that was my downfall. And at the end of the day, I guess I can say that <br>
    that means I don't have regrets. If I was able to make you happy in this past year, then of course<br>
    it was all worth it for you. <br> <br>

    But my god. My god it hurts so much. It hurts so so much. I don't know why I'm even writing this- <br>
